## 3. **Add Update Communication Preferences Endpoint**
__Create a PATCH endpoint to allow users to update their preferences__

```kotlin
// /src/main/kotlin/com/example/app/controllers/UserController.kt
data class UpdateCommunicationPreferencesRequest(
    val communicationPreferences: UserCommunicationPreferences
)

@PATCH(
    "/users/{userId}/communication-preferences",
    consumes = [MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON],
    produces = [MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON]
)
suspend fun updateCommunicationPreferences(
    @PathVariable userId: Long,
    @RequestBody request: UpdateCommunicationPreferencesRequest
): User {
    validateCommunicationPreferences(request.communicationPreferences)
    logger.info("Updating communication preferences for user $userId to ${request.communicationPreferences}")
    return userRepository.updateCommunicationPreferences(userId, request.communicationPreferences)
}
```

